The leaders of Australia, India, and the United States express their shock and sadness at the assassination of former Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe. They acknowledge his transformative leadership and his efforts in strengthening Japanese relations with their respective countries. They also recognize his role in establishing the Quad partnership and his dedication to promoting a free and open Indo-Pacific. They offer their condolences to the people of Japan and Prime Minister Kishida, and pledge to continue working towards peace and prosperity in the region in honor of Prime Minister Abe's memory.